response.body:
{
  "token_issued_at" : "2017-08-04T22:27:20+00:00",
  "client_ip" : "127.0.0.1",
  "account" : "dev",
  "user_agent" : "Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_15_6) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/87.0.4280.88 Safari/537.36",
  "username" : "admin"
}

schema.description: Information about the client making a request

account.description: The account attribute of the client provided access token.

client_ip.description: The request client IP address as determined by Conjur. This same IP address appears in application logs and audit logs.

token_issued_at.description: The issued timestamp, that is, when the provided access token was created (iat field in the JWT)

user_agent.description: The incoming request HTTP user agent header.
user_agent.example: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_15_6) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/87.0.4280.88 Safari/537.36

username.description: The username attribute of the provided access token.
